# Canonical Accounting Invariants Implementation Plan

Goal: Define the immutable laws of the RoboLedgers system to ensure audit-readiness and financial integrity.

## Proposed Sections

### 1. Canonical Transaction Object
- Define the base structure of a transaction.
- Identify immutable vs. mutable (versioned) fields.
- Define fingerprinting triggers.

### 2. Transaction Fingerprinting (txsig)
- Define the hashing algorithm (SHA-256 recommended).
- List exact input fields for the fingerprint.
- Define duplicate handling logic.

### 3. Instrument Polarity Rules
- Define Debit/Credit behavior for Assets, Liabilities, Equity, Revenue, and Expenses.
- Focus on Bank Accounts, Credit Cards, and Crypto.

### 4. Immutability & Mutation Rules
- Define the "No Destruction" policy.
- Detail reversing and adjusting entries.

### 5. Audit Trail Invariants
- Define log requirements for every state change.
- Ensure time-travel capability.

### 6. Reconciliation Invariants
- Define the threshold for "Reconciled" status.
- Block reporting on unreconciled data.

### 7. Debugging & Exception Strategy
- Define the invariant violation error hierarchy.

## Verification Plan
- Cross-check against standard GAAP/IFRS principles.
- Simulated edge cases (duplicates, mid-month reversals).
